00:08:42.100 --> 00:08:45.260
So, the first thing is point
defects, start at zero dimension.

00:08:45.260 --> 00:08:48.420
And, these are localized
disruptions in the regularity

00:08:48.420 --> 00:08:51.830
of the lattice.
How local at the level of one

00:08:51.830 --> 00:08:55.490
lattice site, at the level of one
lattice site. And,

00:08:55.490 --> 00:08:59.160
so there's three types we're going
to look at. The first one is the

00:08:59.160 --> 00:09:02.830
substitutional impurity.
And, if you flip over on the

00:09:02.830 --> 00:09:06.490
backside, I've copied this cartoon.
