00:15:40.770 --> 00:15:44.550
And that's simply an unoccupied
lattice site different from the

00:15:44.550 --> 00:15:48.330
interstitial. It's a site that's
not occupied. And so,

00:15:48.330 --> 00:15:52.110
here's the cartoon. You see this is
a regular atom that hasn't been

00:15:52.110 --> 00:16:11.953
placed on its proper site.
And, we have a vacancy in that

00:15:36.000 --> 00:15:40.000
location. And so,
there's two types of vacancy

00:15:40.000 --> 00:15:44.000
formations. The first is when the
material is being solidified,

00:15:44.000 --> 00:15:48.000
whether it's solidifying from the
liquid, whether it's vapor

00:15:48.000 --> 00:15:52.000
